at|^b@2|at|^^|cp|3|at|^b^*bMarty Bergen: ^*n|
cp||at|The following is worth keeping in mind on all hands. When things look bad, whether because of bad luck or bad bidding, think optimistically. 'What if?' Give yourself a chance. On the other hand, when you are in a contract that looks cold, play devil's advocate. You need to be pessimistic and concern yourself with things going wrong, such as bad splits. Figure out if there is a way that you can survive bad luck rather than complaining about it later on. Certainly subjects such as safety plays should be part of your arsenal.|
